<span sc>Joseph Campbell</span>: Throughout the inhabited world, in all times
and under every circumstance, myths of man have flourished; and they have been
the living inspiration of whatever else may have appeared out of the activities
of the human body and mind.

Further:

<span sc>Joseph Campbell</span>: It would not be too much to say that myth is the secret opening through which
the inexhaustible energies of the cosmos pour into the human cultural
manifestation.
